<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="314" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,150,1097]" pageId="5" pageNumber="314">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1034,1060]" pageId="5" pageNumber="314">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet of the new species is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[1075,1156,1035,1060]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="314">antero-</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1212,1324,1034,1060]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="314">macularis</emphasis>
, referring to the large blotch along the anterior area of the forewing.
</paragraph>
